-- U.S.-based high-yield bond funds post record outflows-Lipper
-- 
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 05:04PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 7 (Reuters) - Investors in U.S.-based funds pulled $7.1 billion out of high-yield bond funds in the week ended Aug. 6, marking their biggest outflows on record, data from Thomson Reuters' Lipper service showed on Thursday.

The outflows were the biggest since Lipper records began in 1992. Investors pulled $4.8 billion out of taxable bond funds overall, marking their biggest outflows since March.